#: ../../source/news/security/istio-security-2019-006/index.rst:6
msgid ""
"Envoy, and subsequently Istio, are vulnerable to the following DoS "
"attack. An infinite loop can be triggered in Envoy if the option "
"``continue_on_listener_filters_timeout`` is set to ``True``. This has "
"been the case for Istio since the introduction of the Protocol Detection "
"feature in Istio 1.3 A remote attacker may trivially trigger that "
"vulnerability, effectively exhausting Envoy’s CPU resources and causing a"
" denial-of-service attack."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/security/istio-security-2019-006/index.rst:15
msgid "Impact and detection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/security/istio-security-2019-006/index.rst:17
msgid ""
"Both Istio gateways and sidecars are vulnerable to this issue. If you are"
" running one of the affected releases, your cluster is vulnerable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/security/istio-security-2019-006/index.rst:21
msgid "Mitigation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/security/istio-security-2019-006/index.rst:23
msgid ""
"Workaround: The exploitation of that vulnerability can be prevented by "
"customizing Istio installation (as described in `installation options "
"</docs/reference/config/installation-options/#pilot-options>`_ ), using "
"Helm to override the following options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/security/istio-security-2019-006/index.rst:28
msgid ""
"{{< text plain >}} –set "
"pilot.env.PILOT_INBOUND_PROTOCOL_DETECTION_TIMEOUT=0s –set "
"global.proxy.protocolDetectionTimeout=0s"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/security/istio-security-2019-006/index.rst:32
msgid ""
